description:
This course is an introductory course for PMI PMP® (Project Management Professional) Test Preparation.

This course consist of 75 questions randomly focusing on the PMBOK® fifth edition (Project Management Body Of Knowledge) process groups (initiating process group, planning process group, executing process group, monitoring and controlling process group, and closing process group). 

As well, this course consist of the knowledge area focus (framework, integration, project scope management, project time management, project cost management, project quality management, project risk management, project human resource management, project stakeholders management).

In this course, you will have the chance to practice on many questions related to PMP (Project Management Professional) in order to gain understanding whether the certificate benefits you prior investing more time.

Materials included in this course are

  • Video (Screen capture of MS PowerPoint and/or PDF).
  • Project management template (tools and techniques) (additional downloadable resources) with each lecture.
title: PMP®: Project Management Professional Test Prep 75+ QA
instructors: MSc, PMOC, PMP®, PRINCE2®, ITIL® Ramzi Abou Rahal
